#. type: Title ==
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Registration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "In order for an application or service to utilize {project_name} it has to register a client in {project_name}.\n"
"An admin can do this through the admin console (or admin REST endpoints), but clients can also register themselves through the {project_name} client\n"
"registration service.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Client Registration Service provides built-in support for {project_name} Client Representations, OpenID Connect Client Meta Data and SAML Entity Descriptors.\n"
"The Client Registration Service endpoint is `/realms/<realm>/clients-registrations/<provider>`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "The built-in supported `providers` are: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "default - {project_name} Client Representation (JSON)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "install - {project_name} Adapter Configuration (JSON)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "openid-connect - OpenID Connect Client Metadata Description (JSON)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "saml2-entity-descriptor - SAML Entity Descriptor (XML)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following sections will describe how to use the different providers. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:20
#: source/server_admin/topics/authentication.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "To invoke the Client Registration Services you usually need a token. The token can be a bearer token, an initial access token or a registration access token.\n"
"There is an alternative to register new client without any token as well, but then you need to configure Client Registration Policies (see below).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bearer Token"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "The bearer token can be issued on behalf of a user or a Service Account. The following permissions are required to invoke the endpoints (see link:{adminguide_link}[{adminguide_name}] for more details):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "create-client or manage-client - To create clients\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "view-client or manage-client - To view clients\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "manage-client - To update or delete client\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you are using a bearer token to create clients it's recommend to use a token from a Service Account with only the `create-client` role (see link:{adminguide_link}[{adminguide_name}] for more details).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Initial Access Token"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "The recommended approach to registering new clients is by using initial access tokens.\n"
"An initial access token can only be used to create clients and has a configurable expiration as well as a configurable limit on how many clients can be created. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "An initial access token can be created through the admin console.\n"
"To create a new initial access token first select the realm in the admin console, then click on `Realm Settings` in the menu on the left, followed by\n"
"`Client Registration` in the tabs displayed in the page. Then finally click on `Initial Access Tokens` sub-tab.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "You will now be able to see any existing initial access tokens. If you have access you can delete tokens that are no longer required. You can only retrieve the\n"
"value of the token when you are creating it. To create a new token click on `Create`. You can now optionally add how long the token should be valid, also how\n"
"many clients can be created using the token. After you click on `Save` the token value is displayed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is important that you copy/paste this token now as you won't be able to retrieve it later. If you forget to copy/paste it, then delete the token and create another one.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "The token value is used as a standard bearer token when invoking the Client Registration Services, by adding it to the Authorization header in the request.\n"
"For example: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Authorization: bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUz...\n"
"----            \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Registration Access Token"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "When you create a client through the Client Registration Service the response will include a registration access token.\n"
"The registration access token provides access to retrieve the client configuration later, but also to update or delete the client.\n"
"The registration access token is included with the request in the same way as a bearer token or initial access token.\n"
"Registration access tokens are only valid once when it's used the response will include a new token. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "If a client was created outside of the Client Registration Service it won't have a registration access token associated with it.\n"
"You can create one through the admin console. This can also be useful if you loose the token for a particular client.\n"
"To create a new token find the client in the admin console and click on `Credentials`. Then click on `Generate registration access token`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "{project_name} Representations"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `default` client registration provider can be used to create, retrieve, update and delete a client.\n"
"It uses {project_name} Client Representation format which provides support for configuring clients exactly as they can be configured through the admin\n"
"console, including for example configuring protocol mappers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "To create a client create a Client Representation (JSON) then do a HTTP POST to `/realms/<realm>/clients-registrations/default`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "It will return a Client Representation that also includes the registration access token.\n"
"You should save the registration access token somewhere if you want to retrieve the config, update or delete the client later. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "To retrieve the Client Representation then do a HTTP GET to `/realms/<realm>/clients-registrations/default/<client id>`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:83
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "It will also return a new registration access token. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "To update the Client Representation then do a HTTP PUT to with the updated Client Representation to:\n"
"`/realms/<realm>/clients-registrations/default/<client id>`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "To delete the Client Representation then do a HTTP DELETE to:\n"
"`/realms/<realm>/clients-registrations/default/<client id>`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "{project_name} Adapter Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/securing_apps/topics/client-registration.adoc:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `installation` client registration provider can be used to retrieve the adapter configuration for a client.\n"
